-- Harper’s Communications Director MacDougall Leaving Post
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-08-14T14:34:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-14/harper-s-communications-director-macdougall-leaving-post.html
Andrew MacDougall, Prime Minister
 Stephen Harper ’s director of communications, is stepping down to
join public relations agency MSLGroup in London.  MSLGroup, a unit of Publicis Groupe SA, said in a  statement 
that MacDougall will stay in the prime minister’s office until
early September before joining the company in November.  MacDougall, who has worked as a spokesman for Harper since
2008, was appointed to his current post in April 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
 targitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  